# Echothink-Patch: 0007-device-identity
# Title: Generate and persist a DPAPI-backed local device identity
# Area: device-identity
# Depends-On: echothink/0006-login-gate.patch (T21 registers and consumes the non-secret readiness prefs this reset path clears)
# Spec-Depends-On: docs/echothink-browser-alpha/t22-define-device-identity-and-dpapi-storage.md
# Browser-Layer-Reason: The browser owns the local device private-key trust boundary. Key generation, DPAPI protection, restart loading, and reset must happen in native browser code so private key material never enters web pages or extension JavaScript; backend services still own enrollment binding, revocation, proof validation, and authorization.
# Preferred-Surface-Checked: preference, extension, native-required (Local State/profile prefs are used only for non-secret metadata; the bundled extension bridge is deferred to T24; private-key generation and DPAPI storage require a browser-owned native component)
# Security-Critical-Areas: none (no network stack, TLS validation, sandbox, renderer internals, downloads, history, bookmarks, password manager, cookies, or DevTools changes)
# Native-Files-Touched: chrome/browser/BUILD.gn, chrome/browser/chrome_browser_main.cc, chrome/browser/chrome_content_browser_client.cc, chrome/browser/echothink/device_identity/device_identity_service.h (new), chrome/browser/echothink/device_identity/device_identity_service.cc (new)
# Rebase-Risk: medium (adds a small browser component, pref registration calls, and a startup ensure call near existing Local State initialization)
# Validation: Apply inherited patches and active Echothink predecessors through echothink/0006-login-gate.patch, then this patch with `patch -p1` against pinned Chromium 148.0.7778.178. Build on Windows and verify with a fresh user data dir: (1) startup creates User Data/Echothink Device Identity/device_key.dpapi; (2) Local State has non-secret installation_id, key_id, ES256 public_key_jwk, key_created_at, key_storage, browser channel/version; (3) restart preserves key_id and installation_id; (4) the protected key file decrypts only through current-user DPAPI in browser code; (5) calling ResetLocalEnrollmentState deletes the protected key file, rotates installation_id, clears profile enrollment/readiness prefs, and re-enables the login gate.
#
# Notes:
# - The private key is generated as ECDSA P-256, serialized as PKCS#8 bytes only
#   inside the browser process, protected with CryptProtectData using current-user
#   DPAPI and CRYPTPROTECT_UI_FORBIDDEN, then written as a base64 DPAPI envelope
#   to the user-data-dir file. The private key bytes and DPAPI blob are not stored
#   in prefs, extension storage, web storage, logs, docs examples, or progress
#   notes.
# - Local State stores only non-secret metadata: installation_id, key_id,
#   key_algorithm, public_key_jwk, key_created_at, key_storage, browser_channel,
#   and browser_version. Profile prefs store only enrollment status metadata and
#   the T20/T21 readiness booleans/timestamps.
# - If a protected key file exists but cannot be unprotected or parsed, this patch
#   does not silently generate a replacement key. A future bridge/UI path can call
#   ResetLocalEnrollmentState explicitly to remove local enrollment state and
#   generate a new unenrolled identity on the next ensure path.
# - T24 owns exposing a narrow extension bridge. This patch exports native helper
#   functions for status/reset/key loading boundaries but does not expose private
#   key material or DPAPI blobs to JavaScript.

--- a/chrome/browser/BUILD.gn
+++ b/chrome/browser/BUILD.gn
@@ -77,6 +77,7 @@ if (is_win) {
   config("browser_win_linker_flags") {
     libs = [
       "credui.lib",
+      "crypt32.lib",  # Echothink device identity DPAPI storage.
       "cryptui.lib",
       "dwmapi.lib",
       "imm32.lib",  # chrome_elf_init.cc
@@ -577,6 +578,8 @@ source_set("core") {
     "chrome_content_browser_client_navigation_throttles.cc",
     "chrome_content_browser_client_navigation_throttles.h",
     "chrome_content_browser_client_receiver_bindings.cc",
